    {
        "type": "instructions",
        "sequence": 7,
        "text": [
            "Preheat your oven to 200\u00b0C (400\u00b0F).",
            "In a mixing bowl, combine the ground beef, chopped onion, minced garlic, salt, and pepper.",
            "Shape the meat mixture into four equal balls.",
            "Roll out one sheet of puff pastry into a large rectangle.",
            "Place one meat ball in the center of the pastry and fold the edges over it to enclose the filling completely.",
            "Repeat this process with the remaining three meat balls and puff pastry sheets.",
            "Brush the top of each pie with beaten egg and sprinkle with sesame seeds.",
            "Place the pies on the baking sheet and bake for about 45 minutes or until golden brown.",
            "Let the pies cool for a few minutes before serving hot."
        ],
